![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/f263bf52-de7f-446f-8ec5-e4dc29f15aed/20240405_121455.jpg)

During a recent episode of The Pat McAfee Show on April 5, host Pat McAfee didn't hold back his thoughts on WWE superstar Dominik Mysterio and the influence of his mother, Rey Mysterio, on his career trajectory.

“If you were to \[brush him aside\], he'd be gone forever. We'd never have to see him again. He'd probably be at that other place in front of 600 people," said McAfee

In his candid remarks, McAfee implied that Dominik owes much of his current position in WWE to his father, Rey Mysterio, a wrestling legend with a storied career. McAfee's comments also subtly shaded AEW, suggesting that Dominik might find himself performing in front of smaller crowds if not for his association with WWE.

The discussion on The Pat McAfee Show highlights the ongoing rivalry and competition between WWE and AEW, two of the biggest wrestling promotions in the world. McAfee's comments not only reflect his personal opinions on Dominik's career prospects but also touch upon larger themes within the wrestling industry, including the role of family legacy and the dynamics between rival promotions.

As the wrestling landscape continues to evolve, conversations like the one on The Pat McAfee Show offer insights into the complexities of talent development, promotion loyalty, and the ever-present competition between wrestling companies. While McAfee's remarks may stir debate among fans and industry insiders alike, they underscore the ongoing drama and intrigue surrounding the world of professional wrestling.